    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-01-15T16:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-01-15T16:45:00-05:00" n="938"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d938">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.1051/350: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-15T16:00:00-05:45"
                            >January 15, 1930—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9. Legation’s despatch No. 1214 October 31, 1929.<note n="48" xml:id="d938fn48"
                        >Not printed.</note> A Guardia court of arbitration [<hi rend="italic">court
                        martial?</hi>] consisting of three American officers and four Nicaraguan
                    officers will try Sergeant Larios for mutiny, sedition, murder, and menaces and
                    threats toward his subordinates. Date for trial not finally set but it will
                    probably begin within a week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
